# File: specs/feature-draft-issue-skill/feature.gherkin
#
# Generated from: specs/feature-draft-issue-skill/requirements.md
# Issues: #4, #116

Feature: Creating Issues Skill
  As a developer or product owner
  I want a guided interview process that produces well-groomed GitHub issues
  So that every feature request is captured in a structured, spec-ready format

  # --- Happy Path (Issue #4) ---

  Scenario: Interactive interview gathers requirements
    Given I invoke "/draft-issue" without unattended mode
    When the skill starts
    Then it asks adaptive questions about the feature need
    And it skips topics I've already addressed

  Scenario: Issue body follows BDD template
    Given the interview is complete
    When the GitHub issue is created
    Then the body contains User Story, Background, Acceptance Criteria, Functional Requirements, and Out of Scope sections
    And acceptance criteria use Given/When/Then format

  # --- Bug Report (Issue #4) ---

  Scenario: Bug report uses defect template
    Given I'm creating an issue for a bug
    When I indicate it's a defect
    Then the issue uses the bug report template
    And it includes reproduction steps, expected/actual behavior, and environment table

  # --- Unattended Mode Historical Behavior (Issue #4, superseded by #116) ---
  # Retained for provenance; behavior is removed as of v6.0.0.

  Scenario: [SUPERSEDED] Automation mode skips interview
    Given unattended mode is active with ".claude/unattended-mode" file present
    And plugin version is prior to v6.0.0
    When I invoke "/draft-issue" with a feature description argument
    Then the skill skips the interview
    And it infers 3-5 acceptance criteria from steering docs

  # ============================================================
  # Added by issue #116 — Readability treatment + deeper interview
  # ============================================================

  # --- Readability (AC5, AC6) ---

  Scenario: Inline review summary replaces open-ended prompts  # AC5
    Given I have completed the interview and the skill has drafted an issue body
    When the skill reaches the Present Draft for Review step
    Then the skill renders an inline structured summary containing Title, User Story one-liner, numbered ACs with Given/When/Then, FRs with MoSCoW priorities, Out of Scope, and Labels
    And it presents an AskUserQuestion with exactly two options: "[1] Approve — create the issue" and "[2] Revise — I'll describe what to change"

  Scenario: Revise path loops until approval  # AC6
    Given the review summary is shown
    When I select "[2] Revise"
    And I provide free-text change instructions
    Then the skill applies the changes to the draft
    And re-renders the summary + menu
    And repeats until I select "[1] Approve"

  # --- Feature vs Bug contrast (AC7) ---

  Scenario: Tables contrast Feature vs Bug templates  # AC7
    Given I'm scanning SKILL.md
    When I reach the template synthesis section
    Then a reference table contrasts the Feature and Bug templates on Opening section, Context section, Reproduction, Expected vs Actual, AC count guidance, FR priority, and Out of Scope

  # --- Document restructure (AC8) ---

  Scenario: Workflow steps use Input/Process/Output subsections and top-of-file Workflow Overview  # AC8
    Given I open SKILL.md
    When I view each workflow step
    Then each step uses explicit "### Input", "### Process", "### Output" subsections
    And steps with human checkpoints also include a "### Human Review Gate" subsection
    And the file opens with a "Workflow Overview" ASCII diagram listing all steps and marking review gates

  # --- Interview depth (AC9, AC11, AC15) ---

  Scenario: Feature interview probes NFRs, edge cases, and related features  # AC9
    Given I classified the issue as a Feature
    And the adaptive-depth heuristic selected the extended path
    When the skill runs the interview step
    Then the interview includes dedicated probing rounds for non-functional requirements, edge cases and error states, and related existing features for consistency

  Scenario: Adaptive depth heuristic selects core for trivial issues  # AC11
    Given Step 4 investigation found 2 files in 1 component
    And the initial description had low vagueness
    When the skill enters the interview step
    Then the heuristic selects the core-depth interview
    And the skill logs a one-sentence explanation of the decision to the user

  Scenario: Adaptive depth heuristic selects extended for complex issues  # AC11
    Given Step 4 investigation found 12 files across 4 components
    When the skill enters the interview step
    Then the heuristic selects the extended-depth interview
    And the skill logs a one-sentence explanation of the decision to the user

  Scenario: Borderline signals bias toward extended depth  # AC15 (FR23)
    Given Step 4 investigation found 10 files in 1 component
    When the skill evaluates the depth heuristic
    Then it selects extended depth because the borderline rule (single component with many files) triggers

  Scenario: User overrides the heuristic's depth decision  # AC15
    Given the skill logged a depth decision of "core"
    When the skill presents the depth-override AskUserQuestion
    And I select "Use extended interview"
    Then the skill emits a one-line session note "(heuristic chose core, user selected extended)"
    And the skill proceeds with the extended interview

  Scenario: Final interview round asks "Anything I missed?"  # AC15 (FR24)
    Given I have answered all structured interview questions
    When the skill approaches Step 5c
    Then the skill asks a one-line free-text probe "Before I play back my understanding, is there anything I haven't asked that matters here?"
    And any non-empty answer is folded into the understanding block

  # --- Playback (AC10, AC16) ---

  Scenario: Understanding check blocks drafting until confirmed  # AC10
    Given I have answered the interview questions
    When the skill transitions toward the Synthesize Issue Body step
    Then the skill first plays back its understanding
    And asks me to confirm or correct via AskUserQuestion
    And the skill does not draft the issue body until I confirm

  Scenario: Core-depth playback is a one-line confirm  # AC16
    Given the skill selected core-depth for this issue
    When the skill reaches the playback step
    Then the playback renders as a single line: "Drafting an issue for {persona} that {outcome}. In-scope: {...}. Out-of-scope: {...}"
    And presents a two-option menu: "[1] Looks right — draft the issue" / "[2] Something's off — let me clarify"

  Scenario: Extended-depth playback is a structured 5-line block  # AC16
    Given the skill selected extended-depth for this issue
    When the skill reaches the playback step
    Then the playback renders a 5-line structured block with Persona, Outcome, ACs outline, Scope in, Scope out
    And presents the same two-option menu

  # --- Review loop soft guard (AC17) ---

  Scenario: Revise loop expands menu after three consecutive revises  # AC17
    Given I am at the Step 7 review summary
    And I have selected "[2] Revise" three consecutive times without approving
    When the next review round is presented
    Then the AskUserQuestion menu expands to three options: "[1] Keep revising", "[2] Reset and re-interview", "[3] Accept as-is"
    And the skill does not auto-terminate the loop

  Scenario: Reset option returns to the interview step  # AC17
    Given the soft-guard menu is shown
    When I select "[2] Reset and re-interview"
    Then the skill returns to Step 5 with the classification and milestone preserved
    And the consecutive-revises counter resets to zero

  Scenario: Accept-as-is proceeds without further changes  # AC17
    Given the soft-guard menu is shown
    When I select "[3] Accept as-is"
    Then the skill proceeds to Step 8 as if "[1] Approve" was selected

  # --- Unattended-mode removal + breaking change plumbing (AC12, AC13, AC18) ---

  Scenario: Skill ignores unattended-mode flag  # AC12
    Given ".claude/unattended-mode" exists in the project directory
    When I invoke "/draft-issue"
    Then the skill runs the full interactive workflow
    And the skill does not check for or act on the flag file

  Scenario: SDLC runner cannot invoke draft-issue  # AC13
    Given the sdlc-runner.mjs STEP_KEYS constant
    When I inspect it
    Then "draftIssue" is not in the list
    And a comment above STEP_KEYS notes that draft-issue is interactive-only as of plugin v6.0.0
    And the regression test asserts STEP_KEYS.includes('draftIssue') === false

  Scenario: Breaking-change sign-post is present in SKILL.md  # AC18
    Given I am reading SKILL.md after the v6.0.0 release
    When I search for "unattended-mode"
    Then I find exactly one reference: the sign-post sentence "As of v6.0.0, /draft-issue no longer honors .claude/unattended-mode. Issue drafting requires interactive input."

  Scenario: Plugin version is a major bump reflecting the breaking change  # AC18
    Given plugin version was v5.2.0
    When the release for issue #116 ships
    Then plugin.json version is "6.0.0"
    And marketplace.json plugin entry version is "6.0.0"
    And CHANGELOG.md [Unreleased] has a "### Changed (BREAKING)" subsection describing the unattended-mode removal

  # --- Automatable explanation (AC14) ---

  Scenario: Automatable-label question explains downstream impact  # AC14
    Given I reach Step 5b
    When the skill presents the automatable-label AskUserQuestion
    Then the question body includes a 1–2 line explanation that references "/write-spec", "/write-code", "/verify-code", and "/open-pr"
    And clarifies that "automatable" controls downstream automation — not drafting itself
